<H3> <TI>   Hata Critical of Murayama Remark on Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Critical of Murayama Remark on Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205023594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 12 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1205023594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 12 May Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On 11 May, Chairman Tomiichi Murayama of the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan stated in Tokyo that he prefer a 
general election under the existing multiseat constituency 
election system. Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata reacted strongly to 
Murayama's remark, saying: "The remark is problematic. If the 
next election should be held under the existing election system, 
why did we have to carry out political reform? Obviously, some 
people do not want political reform." 
  On top of that, Hata stressed he has no intention of 
dissolving the lower house under the multiseat constituency 
system, and said "it is not time for dissolution of the lower 
house." 

</TEXT>

