  [Text] The Japanese Government reportedly explained to the 
ROK Government, in regards to the discovery of 70 kg of 
undeclared plutonium in the Tokaimura nuclear fuel plant, that 
they will soon provide clarification of the truth. 
  A relevant ROK Foreign Ministry official said on 12 May, 
that 
the ROK Government has received an initial reply from the 
Japanese Government to its request for clarification on the 
discovery of a large quantity of undeclared plutonium, and added 
that the ROK Government will take necessary measures after 
watching over how Japan proceeds on its clarification of the 
truth. 

