<F P=103> SK1305104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
authorities must no longer detain Kim In-so and Ham Se-hwan, 
old men who had suffered in prison for more than 30 years, but 
unconditionally send them back to the Northern half of Korea 
where their families and relatives are waiting, urged the 
Ghana-DPRK Friendship Association in a letter sent to the South 
