just and fair behavior in view of humanitarianism and the 
international law, it noted, urging the South Korean Red Cross 
to help so that Kim and Ham may return to the DPRK without delay. 
  The letter strongly demanded that the South Korean 
authorities abrogate the "National Security Law" and set free 
all the prisoners of conscience including unconverted long-term 
prisoners in South Korea. 

