<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Refugee Status Denied, 104 Vietnamese Go Home </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Refugee Status Denied, 104 Vietnamese Go Home </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1205091994 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0716 GMT 12 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1205091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, May 12 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- A total of 
104 Vietnamese illegal immigrants from the Sungai Besi temporary 
camp returned home yesterday under the United Nations High 
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) voluntary repatriation 
(Volrep) programme. 
  Federal Task Force principal assistant director (settlement) 
Kamarulzaman Murad said all those who returned home had not been 
accorded refugee status after screening. 
  A total of 3,054 Vietnamese illegal mmigrants had 
voluntarily 
returned home since the programme was started three years ago. 
  Kamarul said there were some 6,820 boat people at the Sungai 
Besi camp and those who were not repatriated after the expiry of 
the Volrep programme next year would be sent home in stages 
before 1996. 
  Those who returned home under the programme could resettle 
in 
third countries like the United States and Canada under the 
orderly departure programme (ODP) which is only available in 
Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

