<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Team To Leave Earlier If Rod Change `Serious' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Team To Leave Earlier If Rod Change `Serious' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1505025494 Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN in Korean 15 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1505025494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [AFP, YONHAP report from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] The International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] warned 
on 14 May that if the work of replacing the North Korean nuclear 
fuel rods reaches "a serious stage," [simgakhan tangye] the IAEA 
inspection team will suspend its inspection and leave earlier 
than scheduled. 
  IAEA spokesman David Kyd said that the inspection team will 
leave Vienna on 15 May and arrive in Yongbyon, North Korea 
sometime on 17 May. He said that the inspection team will 
confirm whether North Korea has just started regular preparation 
measures to replace the fuel rods at the five megawatt-class 
atomic reactor or it has already reached "a serious stage" of 
carrying out the replacement work such as unloading the nuclear 
rods. He added that the inspection team is scheduled to stay in 
North Korea for eight days, but that their stay there may be 
extended. 

</TEXT>

