armament, keeping a large quantity of plutonium in concealment. 
  Japan can turn into a nuclear power any moment. 
  Japan, however, is now charging the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea with "the nuclear issue." This reminds us of a 
thief afraid of his own shadow and shows Japan's shamelessness. 
  It is a mockery of the Japanese people and the international 
community for the Japanese reactionaries to advertise the "three 
non-nuclear principles." 
  The Japanese reactionaries had better act with discretion, 
clearly mindful that such acts of theirs as leaving the Japanese 
territory as a nuclear base of the United States and pushing 
ahead with the nuclear armament are foolish acts which will 
result in bringing a nuclear disaster to Japan again. 

</TEXT>

