  [Text] Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
describes the DPRK's proposal for replacing the Armistice 
Agreement with a peace agreement and establishing a new peace 
arrangement as a timely and realistic measure to settle the 
nuclear and other acute issues on the Korean peninsula and open 
a new phase in the improvement of DPRK-USA relations and 
inter-Korean relations. 
  The paper says in a by-lined article: 
  To remove military confrontation and the danger of war and 
preserve peace on the Korean peninsula is a vital question 
related to the peaceful reunification of Korea and the future 
